FBIS4-36657 "drnes113_j_94026" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Chief of Staff Emphasizes Adherence to Cease-Fire Chief of Staff Emphasizes Adherence to Cease-Fire JN1106201694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1700 GMT 11 Jun 94 JN1106201694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Staff Brigadier General brother 'Abd-al-Malik al- Sayyani, chief of the General Staff has emphasized that our Armed Forces -- the forces of unity and legitimacy -- have been fully observing the cease-fire resolution decision made by Lieutenant General brother 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the President Council and commander in chief of the Armed Forces, following his meeting with brother Lakhdar Brahimi, the UN secretary general's envoy. He indicated the government's response to the UN Security Council Resolution 924 on the situation in the Republic of Yemen and [word indistinct] and its compliance with all its clauses. In contrast, he added, the gang of rebellion and secession in the [Yemeni] Socialist Party leadership [words indistinct] international legitimacy the way it has engaged in crime and rebelliousness against national legitimacy and standing against national unity and consensus. In statements published by the newspaper 26 SEPTEMBER today, he said our valiant Armed Forces will remain bound by the cease-fire resolution even if the treasonous separatists breach it and no matter what their flimsy pretexts to invite outside interference in their attempt to internationalize the Yemeni crisis. What is taking place in our country, he emphasized, is a domestic affair, which the forces of unity and legitimacy have managed to contain. They have also succeeded in defeating the rebellious elements. He indicated that the great (?role) of the forces of unity and legitimacy to stand up to the gang of apostasy and secession has been reinforced by the remarkable popular cohesion shown by all our people's sectors [words indistinct] to stand behind the fighters in the battle for unity and democracy against the enemies of the Yemeni people and homeland. The Armed Forces that have defended the revolution and its gains are more capable [words indistinct] and aborting all conspiratorial attempts against it.
